          What is the full meaning of helmet?
          1 : a covering or enclosing headpiece of ancient or medieval armor see armor illustration. 2 : any of various protective head coverings usually made of a hard material to resist impact. 3 : something resembling a helmet.

          Is it helm or helmet?
          As nouns the difference between helm and helmet

          is that helm is (nautical) the steering apparatus of a ship, especially the tiller or wheel or helm can be (archaic) a helmet while helmet is a protective head covering.

          Why helmet is named as helmet?

          How much does a motorcycle helmet cost?
          Top-of-the-line motorcycle helmets can be priced over $1000. Extremely affordable, simple ones can be found for under $100. On average, a motorcycle helmet will run you around $150 to $200 for something a bit above the cheapest model you can find.

          What are the different shapes of motorcycle helmets?
          People generally fit into one of three head shapes: long oval, intermediate oval, and round oval. To find out what you've got, ask a friend to take a photo of your head from above. Flatten your hair down as much as possible, because it can obscure your head's shape.

          weight:
          What is a good weight for a motorcycle helmet?
          Full-face helmets range from approximately 1400 to 1800 grams. Once helmet weight reaches about 1650 grams, it becomes harder to mask its weight. Flip-up, or modular, helmets typically weigh more than a comparable sized full-face helmet, due to the mechanism used to flip up the visor.Sep 29, 2017
